@yxshv came up with LMFAO.tech. But we hadn't perfected it yet - it was supposed to just be a feed full of Twitter and Reddit posts. Fetching posts from Twitter and figuring out whether it's a memes or not - is difficult, and we knew this from the start. "Isn't this a bit dull?" I thought. "We should add liking/retweeting and a points system". And maybe a leaderboard to spice things up? And that's exactly what we did! We made it so that liking, retweeting and posting also do the same on Twitter.
We still had a huge problem though - the automated feed pulled still wasn't perfect - the occasional NSFW content, spam, etc made it almost unusable. So we had to implement a moderation system along with it.
